sprint: 2026-07-security-modernization
release: next
resolution: "Adopted Node >=22.13, Bun 1.3.11, TypeScript 6.0.3, ESLint 10, Commander 15, matching Node 22 declarations, and explicit automation constraints for incompatible future majors."
expected_result: Declared engines and peer ranges are mutually compatible and all verification paths pass.
actual_result: "Bun and isolated npm paths pass typecheck, lint, build, 542 tests, audits, and package smokes; PRs #48/#49 supplied live evidence for the intentional constraints."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  monica-security-modernization,related,"2026-07-16T17:04:32.096Z",null,null
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:04:32.096Z",codex-root,Commander 15 requires Node >=22.12; ESLint 10.7 requires >=22.13 on the Node 22 line.
  "2026-07-16T17:19:06.884Z",codex-root,Post-merge Dependabot PR #49 proposed @types/node 26.1.1. It passed mechanically but was closed because the declared runtime remains Node 22; >=23 type-major updates are ignored to preserve runtime/type alignment.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:04:32.096Z",codex-root,TypeScript 7.0.2 is intentionally deferred because @typescript-eslint 8.64.0 declares TypeScript <6.1.0.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:04:32.096Z",codex-root,@types/node should match the supported runtime line rather than always follow the registry latest major.
